<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT January 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The Afghan Taliban militia Thursday overran a
provincial capital following its recapture of a strategic airbase
from the opposing factions, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Defense Minister Igor Rodionov said Thursday
Russia plans no new military alliances in response to the planned
eastward expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO).
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Indian trade union leader and former parliament
member Dr. Datta Samant was shot dead by unidentified gunmen near
his residence in Mumbai (Bombay) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea's Seoul District Court Thursday sentenced
a U.S. soldier, Eric Munnich Stephen, to 15 years in prison for
murder.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Large numbers of Israeli soldiers, police, and
border policemen have been brought in to Hebron to ensure a
smooth redeployment in the city, which is expected soon after the
Knesset gives its approval Thursday. 
</P>
