<HEADLINE> Breakthrough in Sino-U.S. Scientific Relations(3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Professor Zhou Guangzhao described
the Sino-U.S. scientific meeting as "very successful, very
important."
</P>
<P>
"The talks between us covered major issues faced by the two
countries and the world as a whole, including the changed
scientific and technological environment, sustainable development,
enhancing the partnership between scientists of the two countries,
particularly the contacts between young scientists -- the future
scientific leaders of the two countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to Xinhua, Dr. Alberts said that it is essential for
the future and for humanity that the scientists of the two
countries work together closely on their common goal.
</P>
<P>
"The future of the world depends on the intelligent use of
science and technology and the expanse of population," he said,
"It is clear that in the next century, China and U.S. will be the
leading countries of the world."
</P>
<P>
"During the meeting between the top leaders of the two
academies, we discoved that we have the same goals, and have both
the need and ability to work together closely," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The U.S. academy has limited financial resources to use for
our international affairs. But we intend to devote most of those
resources in the coming years to facilitating our activities with
Chinese scientists," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our focus will be the programs that brings together the most
outstanding young scientists of our two countries, who represent
the future leaders in science and technology in China and the
United States," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We view this as important investment for the future of science
as well as for the future of a friendly and cooperative
relationship between our two countries," he added.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
