<HEADLINE> Two Explosions Rock Clinic Building in Atlanta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Two explosions rocked a
building containing an abortion clinic north of Atlanta this
morning, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The first explosion occurred at 9:30 a.m. (1430 GMT) at Atlanta
Northside Family Planning Services, located on the ground floor of
a five-story building that also houses offices of lawyers,
dentists and other professionals.
</P>
<P>
The second explosion happened about 10:35 a.m. and appeared to
come in the parking lot outside, possibly in a trash container.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately clear whether there are any injuries in
the first blast, but some injuries were reported in the second
explosion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
