<HEADLINE> 500 Die of Aids Weekly in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's cumulative aids
cases had soared to more than 200,000 by the end of 1996, forcing
National Aids Control Program (NACP) officials to decide to
embark on a concernted awareness campaign this year.
</P>
<P>
With an estimated 1.2 million Zimbabweans now having the HIV
virus which causes AIDS, the NACP will this year mobilize all
available resources to curb the pandemic, NACP Coordinator
Evaristo Marowa said here today.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''the AIDS situation continues to worsen,... with 500
AIDS-related death per week."
</P>
<P>
"The situation will unfortunately continue to be a cause of
concern in 1997, owing to the large number of people already with
HIV,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
''In 1997 focus will be on strong sustainable political
mobilization so that a substantive supporting environment is
provided for AIDS prevention and control,'' he said. enditem

