<HEADLINE> Biggest Flyover in Southwest China Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The biggest highway flyover in
southwest China opened to traffic today in Chengdu, capital of
Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The 4,250-meter-long flyover, the "Qinglong", cost 320 million
yuan to build.
</P>
<P>
Two main highways from Chengdu to Chongqing and Mianzhu cities
have also been connected to the flyover. Cars were crossing it
today at the rate of 20 vehicles a minute.
</P>
<P>
The flyover will help reduce worsening traffic jams in the
northern part of the city.
</P>
<P>
Losses to the city caused by traffic jams will be slashed by a
big margin. The losses are estimated to have cost millions of yuan
in the past few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
