<HEADLINE> OTE to Make More Profits for 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The Hellenic Telecommunications
Organization (OTE) has said it would be recording profits for 1997
totaling 304 billion drachmas (1.32 billion U.S. dollars),
compared to 250 billion drachmas (1.04 billion dollars) in 1996,
an increase of about 22 percent.
</P>
<P>
Accrdoing to the recently approved general budget, the OTE's
income for 1997 is estimated at 840 billion drachmas (3.5 billion
dollars), and over 1 trillion drachmas (4.2 billion dollars) for
1998.
</P>
<P>
The organization's expenditures for 1997 are estimated at 535
billion drachmas (2.2 billion dollars), a 9.5 percent increase
on the 1996 figure of 488 billion drachmas (2 billion dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
