<HEADLINE> Two Explosions Blasts at Clinic Building in Atlanta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Two explosions blasted in
and out of a clinic building in Atlanta today, leading to some
injuries, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The first blast occurred at 9:30 a.m. (1430 GMT) at the Atlanta
Northside Family Planning Services, located on the ground floor of
a five-story building that also houses offices of lawyers,
dentists and other professionals.
</P>
<P>
The explosion shattered glass of the building, sending debris
to a large area outside the building. No injuries were reported in
that explosion, which appeared to come from the first floor.
</P>
<P>
An hour later, another explosion blasted from a trash container
outside the building. Some injuries were reported including an
agent of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms, who was
investigating the first blast, but no one was seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
Two cars near the trash container were badly damaged in the
second explosion.
</P>
<P>
In July last year, a mass explosion erupted in the Centennial
Olympic Park in Atlanta when the Olympic Games were being held in
the city. The blast killed two people, and injuring more than 100
others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
