<HEADLINE> Swans Land in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Nature treated local people in
Nevrokopi, Drama and surrounding villages in northern Greece to a
rare sight this morning when they awoke to find that dozens of
swans had landed for a rest after migrating from countries of
northern Europe.
</P>
<P>
The country's forestry officials held that the swans, who
appeared to be hungry and exhausted, had migrated from the north,
possibly Russia, where temperatures are below freezing.
</P>
<P>
In order to protect the swans from unscrupulous hunters, the
local forestry department issued an announcement "advising"
people not to harm the birds.
</P>
<P>
If the cold weather continued in northern Europe, more swans
and other rare birds could be expected in Greece, said the
forestry officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
