<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Has Nothing to Do With Sudan's Political </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- President Negasso Gidada
said today Ethiopia is not responsible for the political problem
in Sudan.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the president said
Ethiopia has nothing to do with Sudan's political problem when
talking with outgoing ambassador of Lesotho J.T. Mestings here.
</P>
<P>
President Negasso said the instability in Sudan is the
creation of the Sudanese government which failed to pay due
attention to efforts being exerted by member countries of the
Inter-Governmental Authority on Development (IGAD) including
Ethiopia to peacefully solve the problem in Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The Sudan People's Liberation Army which took up arms against
Khartoum since 1983, seized two border towns recently in an
offensive which is now continuing.
</P>
<P>
Gidada charged that Sudan is engaged in disrupting peace in
neighboring countries including Ethiopia, at a time when Ethiopia
is striving to do everything in her capacity to defuse the
conflict in that country.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Foreign Ministry issued a statement here on
Tuesday in connection of the Sudanese government's accusation of
Ethiopian forces shelling two border towns of Sudan.
</P>
<P>
It denied shelling Sudan's border towns but criticized
Khartoum for externalizing its internal conflicts. 
</P>
