<HEADLINE> Germany, Ethiopia Sign Coop Pacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Germany today granted
ethiopia 9.5 million U.S. Dollars to help Addis to get over its
difficulties, the Ministry of Economic Development and
Cooperation said in a press release here today.
</P>
<P>
The two countries signed six technical cooperation agreements
to this effect.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total grant, 2.5 million Dollars is allocated for
the settlement of demobilized servicemen, 2.3 million dollars for
the land-use and resources management project, 2.1 million
dollars for self-help fund with a view to improving economic and
living conditions of the target population.
</P>
<P>
The balance will go to financing advisory assistance to Forest
administration, research on bamboo management and other projects.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, these specific technical
cooperation agreements were part of the pledges previously made
by the German government to support the projects in Ethiopia.
