thanked King Hussein of Jordan and President Hosni Mubarak of
Egypt for their support in reaching an agreement between the
Israelis and Palestinians on the Israeli troops' pullback from the
West Bank city of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
National Security Adviser-designated Samuel Berger revealed in
an interview with network radio reporters that the thank was given
through morning phone calls.
</P>
