without the intervention of King Hussein and the support of
President Mubarak. Last weekend, King Hussein put forward a
compromise proposal concerning Israeli redeployment in the West
Bank rural areas, which finally rescued negotiations between the
Israelis and Palestinians from collapse, and helped conclude the
Hebron deal.
</P>
<P>
Berger said Netanyahu, Arafat, King Hussein and Mubarak are all
expected to visit Washington separately in the coming months, but
said no summit was planned.
</P>
<P>
"This is not a big summit. This will be a series of meetings,"
he said. 
