<HEADLINE> Six Injured in Explosions in Atlanta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Six people were injured in
two explosions in and out of a clinic building in Atlanta today,
said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The first blast occurred at 9:30 a.m. (1430 GMT) at the Atlanta
Northside Family Planning Services, located on the ground floor of
a five-story building that also houses offices of lawyers,
dentists and other professionals.
</P>
<P>
The explosion shattered windows across the street and sent
debris to a large area outside the building. No injuries were
reported in that explosion.
</P>
<P>
An hour later, another explosion blasted from a trash container
outside the building. Six people were injured, including an agent
of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms, who was
investigating the first blast. Four of them were hospitalized,
but were in stable condition.
</P>
<P>
Two cars near the trash container were badly damaged in the
second explosion.
</P>
<P>
After the explosions, police evacuated everyone within 500
meters of the building.
</P>
<P>
Investigation were under way, but police said that it appeared
that the abortion clinic was the target of the explosion. A half
hour after the second explosion, the Piedmont Clinic, another
abortion center in the city, was evacuated after receiving a bomb
threat.
</P>
<P>
In July last year, a mass explosion erupted in the Centennial
Olympic Park in Atlanta when the Olympic Games were being held in
the city. The blast killed two people, and injured more than 100
others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
