<HEADLINE> More Companies Registered in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 50,000 new companies
were registered in Hong Kong in 996, according to figures
released today by the Registry of Companies.
</P>
<P>
There are 49,734 new companies registered in 1996, 16,726 more
than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the total number of companies registered
under the Companies Ordinance had reached 483,181, a rise of 2.4
percent over 471,883 by December 31, 1995.
</P>
<P>
Gordon Jones, the registrar of Companies said that the figures
indicated an increase of activities in all major business sectors
in Hong Kong in 1996, compared with 1995.
</P>
<P>
The total number of overseas companies registered in Hong Kong
stood at 4,604 by the end of 1996, up 287 from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The number of new overseas companies registered in Hong Kong
last year was 665, an increase of 14 percent over the previous
year.  
</P>
