<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Fugitive Lawmaker Finally Captured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A fugitive congressman was
finally captured today after 23 days of hiding in the country.
</P>
<P>
Remeo Jalosjos, a representative from Zamboanga del Norte
province, was arrested this afternoon by the Presidential Security
Group (PSG) and the 250th Air Force Wing on an Island off Bagac,
Bataan province in the west of Manila Bay.
</P>
<P>
Receiving the long-awaited news, Philippine President Fidel
Ramos commended the PSG for "a job well done".
</P>
<P>
Jalosjos, who is wanted for raping an 11 year old girl, was
cornered by a 100-man operatives of the PSG and National Bureau of
Investigation, which used six helicopters and several cars in the
operation.
</P>
<P>
A wife of one of Jalosjos' henchmen tipped the PSG on the
whereabouts of Jalosjos, who did not resist capture and was
brought immediately to the PSG headquarters in the Presidential
Palace.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation said that Jalosjos was planning to flee
the country by flying to Cebu before proceeding to Tawi-Tawi where
he would take a high speed pumpboat to Labuan, Malaysia. From
Labuan, he would fly to London apparently under an assumed name.
</P>
<P>
The Regional Trial Court of Makati in Metro Manila issued a
warrant last December 26 for the arrest of Jalosjos for two
counts of statutory rape and 12 counts of acts of lasciviousness.
</P>
<P>
However, the police failed to find him at his several
residences. A nationwide manhunt was immediately launched for his
capture. In fact the manhunt extended up to Indonesia following
reports that Jalosjos fled to that country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
