<HEADLINE> 71 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Gendarme soldiers have
seized 71.2 kilograms of heroin and 88.6 kilograms of hashish in
recent anti-drug trafficking operations in southeastern Turkey and
arrested seven people in the connection.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today that the
heroin was found in raids on two heroin workshops in Baskaletown
of Van province bordering Iran.
</P>
<P>
But the report did not say exactly when the operations were
carried out.
</P>
<P>
Five people suspected of involvement in drug trafficking were
arrested for questioning, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the agency said that the gendarmes
seized 88.6 kilograms of hashish and detained two suspected drug
smugglers in Lice town of Diyarbakir, center of southeastern
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Turkish police seized 3 tonnes of heroin in 1996, accounting
for 22 percent of the world's total haul, and 7 tonnes of hashish
in the same year, according to latest official figures.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 4,000 people including 136 foreigners were detained on
drug-related charges during the year, said the Anatolia News
Agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
