<HEADLINE> Vice Premier Urges Effective Help for People in Difficulty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- China's vice premier Wu Bangguo
today urged government officials to take effective measures to
help urban families suffering difficulties in their daily lives.
</P>
<P>
At a national telephone conference, Wu said that it was
essential to make concerted efforts to tackle the problems as the
traditional Spring Festival celebration draws near.
</P>
<P>
"Life problems have a major bearing on people's interests, not
only as an economic problem but also a political one," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, a number of state-owned enterprises suffered
losses and defaulted on workers' wages. This in turn led to
difficulties for some workers in their day to day lives, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Life was also hard for some retired workers, the elderly and
disabled, as China still lacked a comprehensive social security
system, he said.
</P>
<P>
The central authorities have attached great importance to the
issue, and worked out a series of policies and measures to deal
with the situation, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials at various levels should carry out the
policies and measures in earnest, and help in practical ways
people without adequate food, clothing, housing and medical care,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Local governments and enterprises should make sure the jobless
and pensioners get basic wages or pensions to ensure a normal
daily life in the festive season, the vice premier stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
