<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Volcano Erupts, Thousands Evacuated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's most active volcano
Mt. Merapi erupted twice this morning while thousands of residents
were evacuated, the Antara News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The first eruption occurred around 10:35 a.m. local time (0335
GMT), and the second one followed three minutes later, said an
official of the Volcanology Office's observatory in Kaliurang,
located at the slope of Mt. Merapi.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported as authorities evacuated thousands
of villagers away from the declared danger zones of Turgo, Tritis
and Kaliurang towns.
</P>
<P>
The eruption emitted hot lava that flowed six kilometers down
towards Boyong, Krasak and Bebeng rivers.
</P>
<P>
Mt. Merapi, measuring 2,968 meters high and one of the 127
volcanoes in the country, is situated in Central Java, the most
densely populated region on Java island.
</P>
<P>
The volcano's activities could be seen from Yogyakarta, some 25
kilometers south of the volcano. Thousands of people in the city
came out on the streets to watch the scene, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The danger level of the Mt. Merapi has been raised to "alert"
-- the highest warning level in Indonesia for volcanic activities.
</P>
<P>
The last eruption of Mt. Merapi was on November 22, 1994, when
it spewed hot lava and rained six kilometers of volcanic ashes,
killing more than 60 people and injuring dozens.
</P>
<P>
Merapi is classified as one of the most active volcanoes in the
world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970117.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Jobless Rate Remains Unchanged for Eight Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Jobless rate in the European
Union (EU) stood unchanged at 10.9 percent for eight months as of
November 1996, Eurostat, the EU's statistical office said today.
</P>
<P>
In the month, about 18 million people were out of work in EU
countries.
</P>
<P>
Most significant falls in unemployment rate over the 12 months
until November were reported in Britain, Denmark, Finland, Belgium
and Ireland, according to Eurostat.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, the jobless rate rose from 8.5 percent to 9.3
percent in Germany and from 11.8 percent to 12.5 percent in France
in the same period, Eurostat said.
</P>
<P>
In November, Luxembourg and Austria enjoyed the lowest rates of
3.3 percent and 4.0 percent respectively while Spain and Finland
had the highest rates of 22.3 percent and 15.3 percent, separately.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate was 5.4 percent in the United States and 3.4
percent in Japan in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
