<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong, Guangdong Agree On Boundary of Administration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A Memorandum of Understanding
(MOU) concerning the Boundary of Administration between Hong Kong
and south China's Guangdong Province was initialed today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement defines a clear boundary of administration for
all sectors -- the land boundary between the New Territory in
northern Hong Kong and Shenzhen, the boundary in Deep Bay and Mirs
Bay, and the sea boundary to the west, south and east of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
John Ashton, deputy political adviser to the Hong Kong British
government, and Xiao Jinzhe, deputy director general of the
Foreign Affairs Office of the Guangdong Provincial government,
initialed the agreement in Shenzhen, Guangdong Province, today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is the outcome of 13 rounds of talks between Hong
Kong and Guangdong, which began in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference in Hong Kong this afternoon,
Ashton described the agreement as a good outcome for Hong Kong.
"The boundary between Hong Kong and Guangdong is one of the
busiest in the world. Millions of people cross it every month, as
do large numbers of cars, lorries, ships and boats, carrying a
formidable and growing amount of cross-border trade."
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong official acknowledged that management of such a
boundary poses a special challenge to all the agencies involved on
each side, from police and customs authorities to those
responsible for flood control and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
"The task is clearly easier if both sides know and agree upon
exactly where the boundary runs at every point. It is good news
for every one concerned with policing the boundary and managing
cross-border activities." said Ashton.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970117.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Special Envoy Visits Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mogadishu, january 17 (Xinhua) -- The Italian Special Envoy to
Somalia, Gusepe Cassini, held talks with Somali faction leader
Hussein Mohamed Aidid here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Cassini asked Hussein Aidid to lift the Persona Non Grate
issued against the European Speical Envoy to Somalia, Sigurd
Illing, sources close to the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
However, no conclusion has been made over the issue.
</P>
<P>
Cassini told Hussein Aidid that the Italian government will
support a broad based administration in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The Italian envoy, who is based in Nairobi, Kenya, is expected
to meet another faction leader Ali Mahdi Mohamed this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The envoy arrived here yesterday afternoon. enditem

