<HEADLINE> Police Net Robbers, Thieves and Sheep Stealers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Police in China have solved
more than 189,000 criminal cases, uncovered 23,000 criminal gangs
and arrested 9,998 suspects since the start of the winter.
</P>
<P>
Police in China's capital of Beijing have focused on bicycle
thieves and thefts of motor vehicles, as well as house break-ins.
</P>
<P>
By December 15, Beijing police officers had caught 1,900
bicycle thieves, smashed 24 gangs, and recovered or found 13,000
stolen bikes. Around 9,000 of the cycles have already been
returned to their owners.
</P>
<P>
In early December, Beijing Municipal Public Security Bureau
caught suspects Duan Xu and Qi Lirong in the north China port city
of Qinghuangdao. The two robbery suspects had been charged with
stealing 4.4 million yuan (about 530,000 US dollars) of cash by
using narcotics to dope their victims.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing officers have also caught nine people in a gang
responsible for stealing 135,000 yuan by forcing open 10 cash
safes.
</P>
<P>
In central China's Hubei Province, police have dealt mainly
with major cases, gangs and offenders. In just one month police
officers cracked 3,150 criminal cases and caught 227
suspects. Police in the province also smashed 382 gangs, netting
1,700 gangsters.
</P>
<P>
In the provincial capital of Wuhan, police solved a case in
which bank robbers escaped with over one million yuan from a
savings bank on October 25, 1995.
</P>
<P>
In Hubei's Yichang City, police seized suspects Liao Zhengjun
and Huang Zhongxing who staged a highway robbery in which they had
passed themselves off as policemen and hijacked and attacked a
truck driver.
</P>
<P>
In north China's largest port city Tianjin, police cracked 282
criminal cases, confiscated 152 illegally-held guns and 209
knives. On December 27, police arrested Wei Tonghong, who had been
accused of breaking into houses three times and raping women last
autumn.
</P>
<P>
In north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, police
recently rounded up 110 sheep that had been taken by sheep
stealers in September last year.
</P>
<P>
The strike-hard campaign on criminals will continue throughout
the winter months, vowed officials at the Ministry of Public
Security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
