<HEADLINE> Agricultural Bank Praised for Notable Contribution to Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
(ABC) was praised today for making remarkable contributions to
agricultural reform, the government's anti-inflation efforts, and
the restructuring of rural banking.
</P>
<P>
The accolade came from People's Bank of China (PBC) Governor
Dai Xianglong at a meeting with a group of ABC officials in
Beijing today. PBC is China's central bank.
</P>
<P>
ABC has been a major financial supporter of the country's rural
areas, where the current national economic reform was initiated,
said Dai. He stressed that rural reforms have activated reform in
cities, and the increasing income of farmers has helped in the the
development of cities and industries.
</P>
<P>
China, as an agriculture-based country, uses farm products to
account for more than half of the 300 items selected in preparing
the country's price index. This means that inflation is closely
linked to agricultural production, Dai said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that efforts by the bank to meet the financial
requirements of the countryside have been a key factor in the
bumper grain harvests over the past three successive years, which
has been helpful in the successful control of inflation in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The top banker also spoke highly of the contribution made by
the bank in the ongoing restructuring of the country's rural
banking sector.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the bank will further reinforce its
internal management and administration, as well as internal
reforms, and try to become an efficient, standardized state-owned
commercial undertaking with a strong ability to counter risks.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, by the end of last year, ABC had
894.3 billion yuan in bank deposits and 776.9 billion yuan in
outstanding loans, up 28.9 percent and 18.4 percent
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
