<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Communication Bank Praised for Commercialization Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Communications Bank has
set a good example for domestic state banks on their way to
becoming commercialized and operating in line with international
standards.
</P>
<P>
Those were the views expressed in Beijing today by Dai
Xianglong, governor of People's Bank of China, the central bank,
during a meeting with a group of local bankers.
</P>
<P>
Dai said that the bank has been fruitful in preventing risks by
attaching greater importance to the quality of loans, instead of
blindly giving out more loans and setting up more branches.
</P>
<P>
The bank, which has much smaller assets compared with the four
largest state-owned banks in the country, generated nearly 5.4
billion yuan in profits, ranking third among all banks in China,
according to the governor.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that by the end of last year, the bank
had 227.7 billion yuan in deposits and 148.7 billion yuan in
outstanding loans, up 24.8 percent and 22.7 percent, respectively,
over the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
