<HEADLINE> Locals Demand Government Action on Leaning Tower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Pisa mayor Thursday led a
demonstration to demand government action on the protection of the
famous Leaning Tower.
</P>
<P>
The tower has been closed for the past seven years since it
became shaky.
</P>
<P>
Experts kept on arguing about how to stabilize it but so far no
actual work has been carried out.
</P>
<P>
About 500 people joined Thursday's demonstration.
</P>
<P>
Undersecretary for cultural affairs, Alberto La Volpe, told
local television on the same day that the Senate Education
Committee has just approved a bill adding 12 billion lire (7.75
million U.S. dollars) to the 34 billion lire (22 million dollars)
fund for the tower.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Piero Floriani seemed unimpressed by the promise.
</P>
<P>
"We will not feel safe until the bill has been approved by the
Chamber of Deputies (the lower house of parliament) too," he said.
</P>
<P>
"However, we recognize that this is an important step," the
mayor added. 
</P>
