<HEADLINE> 23rd General Population Conference to Open in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A six-day international
conference to discuss the key problems and general growth trend of
the Chinese population will be held in Beijing in mid-October.
</P>
<P>
The 23rd General Population Conference, the first of its kind
in China, will be jointly sponsored by the Demographic Society of
China, the State Family Planning Commission and the International
Union of the Scientific Study of Population.
</P>
<P>
Attending will be about 2,000 population control experts,
economists, public health and family planning workers and the
representatives from the international organizations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and foreign scholars will discuss the most important
issues related to the Chinese population at a one-day forum to be
held in Beijing before the conference.
</P>
<P>
The International Union of the Scientific Study of Population
was founded in 1928, with its headquarters in Belgium. It focuses
on the population problems in developing countries.
</P>
<P>
China is the most populous developing country in the world.
During the past several decades, it has made remarkable progress
in controlling the rapid population growth.
</P>
<P>
The Demographic Society of China is a non-governmental academic
society, which was founded in February of 1981. It now has more
than 2,000 members and over 200 branch organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
