<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
met with Jorma Ollila, president of the Nokia Corporation here
today, to discuss further cooperation between China and this
telecommunications giant of Finland.
</P>
<P>
Wu told Jorma Ollila that the friendly ties between China and
Finland have provided favorable conditions for cooperation between
the two sides.
</P>
<P>
He added China's rapid economic growth and the greater role
information is playing in the country's national economy have
helped open a big market in China for the telecommunications
industry.
</P>
<P>
Wu said Nokia, as one of China's major telecommunications
partners, has maintained good cooperative relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Wu expressed the hope that Nokia will make greater efforts in
technology transfer, localization of products and other fields in
order to develop its long-term involvement in China.
</P>
<P>
Nokia's mobile telecommunications equipment has been introduced
in six Chinese provinces. And the Beijing Nokia Mobile
Telecommunications Ltd., established in 1995, produced 115,000
mobile phones, and scored a 1.2-billion-yuan sales volume.
</P>
<P>
Ollila said China is one of Nokia's top five markets worldwide,
and its business in China has developed satisfactorily over the
past two years, he said.
</P>
<P>
Nokia will continue to expand the production capacity of its
joint ventures in China through technological cooperation,
according Ollila.  
</P>
