<HEADLINE> Ugandan Women Protest Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A peaceful march was organised
by a women pressure group here today to honour women killed in
the recent wave of domestic violence in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The march, attended by hundreds of people mostly of women and
children, started from Nakulabye, where a girl was hacked to
death by her boy friend on december 25, 1996, and ended at the
constitutional square at noon.
</P>
<P>
A memorial service protected by dozens of policemen was also
held at the square under the heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
According to organiser of the march Sheila Kawamara, the march
and service are aimed to put an end to the culture against women
in domestic violence.
</P>
<P>
Several other incidents of domestic violence were reported
over Christmas. On December 25, 1996, a woman called Funa Naluba,
in Eastern District of Mbale was killed by her husband for giving
away a piece of Christmas meat to a neighbour. 
</P>
