charge of plotting to destabilize Sierra Leone's civilian
government adjourned today and will reopen on Monday,
prosecution witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
Among the accused are Major John Koroma, a woman sergeant
named Omopeh Bangura and other six servicemen.
</P>
<P>
Saio Mansaray, a former bodyguard to former President Joseph
Momoh, earlier claimed that one of the accused "attempted to
draft him into their plans to overthrow the government on August
28 last year."
</P>
<P>
A senior military intelligence officer, identified as Dudley
Macfoy, also claimed the same experience at the court.
</P>
<P>
Dudley, also a former senior security officer to deposed
president Valentine Strasser, said the plotters had shown him
part of their ammunitions and told him that 40 men would take
part in the coup.
</P>
<P>
Court sources said 12 more witnesses will be summoned for the
trial, which started five days ago and is to last six weeks.
</P>
