<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A 14-member delegation of the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP) has arrived in Mindanao
in southern Philippines to assess the development situation in the
area, a Philippine News Agency report said today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the delegation, which arrived Thursday, will
seek recommendations on how the program can support the Philippine
government's development initiatives on poverty alleviation,
environment and governance.
</P>
<P>
