<HEADLINE> PLA Troops Qualified for Stationing in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Extensive training and other
preparations made by the People's Liberation Army troops to be
stationed in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) are
progressing smoothly, according to top Chinese military officials.
</P>
<P>
Following an examination conducted by the Chinese PLA
Headquarters of the General Staff, the General Logistics
Department and the General Political Department, the three units
held that the troops are qualified for their work in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Ziren, political commissar of the troops, said education
courses focused on patriotism were given to the officers and
soliders over the past year, and their senses of duty,
responsibility, and honor have been enhanced.
</P>
<P>
In order to better fulfill their task in Hong Kong, troops also
established a regular training order and studied the military
thoughts of Mao Zedong and Deng Xiaoping as well as other military
principles.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with journalists, officers and soldiers were
articulate in their answers to questions on Basic Law of the Hong
Kong SAR. the Garrison Law and other Hong Kong laws.
</P>
<P>
Journalists were also impressed by the troops' orderly
barracks, and their outstanding display of military skill.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhenwu, commander of the troops, and Xiong Ziren said the
troops are first-class, powerful and civilized military forces,
and they can easily reassure the country and win the trust of the
Hong Kong people.  
