<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Indians gathered
outside the residence of trade union leader Dr. D. Samant, who was
gunned down Thursday, in northeast Mumbai (Bombay) today before
the funeral was held.
</P>
<P>
The funeral had to be delayed by four hours because of the
increasing crowds, which included leaders of the state and
political parties from across the country.
</P>
