<HEADLINE> Share Prices Surge on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices surged on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
rose sharply to gain 23.85 points to close at 2,244.21 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 302.09 million units,
valued at 640.84 million Singapore dollars (about 457.74 million
US dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines 280 to 78, while 235
other counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
SMB United was the most actively traded stock as it registered
a turnover of 35.62 million units. It was followed by MBF Holdings
which had 9.85 million shares traded. Kim Eng warrant97 was next
with 9.24 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers as
it rose by 90 cents to finish at 28.9 Singapore dollars. The
Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign was next
picking up by 80 cents to close at 19.1 Singapore dollars, while
the City Development ended 70 cents higher at 13.5 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, GE Life was the biggest loser as it declined
by 40 cents to close at 23.5 dollars. CMSPort fell by 15 cents to
5.4 Hong Kong dollars, while Prima was 12 cents lower at 4.8
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
