<HEADLINE> China's Nuclear Industry Vows to Reduce Economic Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- China's nuclear industry has
set a goal to reduce economic losses by 50 million yuan (about six
million US dollars) in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The target will be met mainly by the Nuclear Fuel Bureau, China
Nuclear Jinyuan Uranium Industry Corporation, and China Baoyuan
Industrial and Trade Corporation, which are under the management
of the China National Nuclear Corporation (CNNC).
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the three subsidiaries signed responsibility
contracts with their parent company at an annual working
conference of the CNNC, which concluded in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
CNNC will honor or penalize the leaders at the end of the year
based on their performance in reducing economic losses. 
