<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 140,000 Overseas-Backed Enterprises Becoming Operational in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 140,000
overseas-funded enterprises had become operational in China by the
end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (Moftec) shows that China has actually used 177.7
billion U.S. dollars of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
According to Moftec, China has so far approved the
establishment of 284,000 foreign direct investment projects,
involving a contractual overseas investment of 467.2 billion
U.S. dollars. A total of 17 million people are employed by
overseas-backed enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the country made actual use of 42.6 billion
U.S. dollars of overseas funds last year, up 13.6 percent compared
with the 1995 figure, despite the fact that the country posted a
drop in both the number of the newly-approved overseas-funded
projects and the volume of the promised use of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
Investment structure has been further improved, and more
technology-intensive and fund-intensive overseas-funded
enterprises have been set up.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, China's foreign trade volume totalled 289.9
billion U.S. dollars, up 3.2 percent over 1995. The country
listed big increases in the number of contracts signed for import
and export of technologies and complete sets of equipment as well
as the sum of money involved in the contracts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 85 countries signed agreements in 1996 to accept
loans from China. It also signed governmental frame agreements
with 22 countries of Asia, Africa and Latin America to provide 24
preferential loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
