<HEADLINE> 6 Killed in Philippine Army, Muslim Rebels Encounter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Six persons were killed and two
others wounded in a renewed encounter between the Philippine
government troopers and Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF)
rebels in Buldon, Maguindanao province, on Thursday, a military
official revealed today.
</P>
<P>
Noel Detoyato, spokesman of the Army's Sixth Infantry Division,
identified the fatalities on their side are two soldiers belonging
to the division's 39th battalion stationed in nearby Parang town,
also in Maguindanao.
</P>
<P>
The military accounted some four casualties on the MILF side
but failed to identify them.
</P>
<P>
The military casualties were part of the reinforcement team
that aided the convoy of Buldon town Mayor Makarampat Manalao, who
were earlier waylaid by some 50 MILF rebels while on their way to
the town.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Fortunato Abat, chairman of the government panel who
is holding peace talks with the MILF and Ghadzali Jaafar, MILF's
vice chairman for political affairs, both said the matter will be
brought up during their second round of low level talks on
February 24-25.  
</P>
</TEXT>
