<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria's Olympic Team World's Best in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Olympic gold-winning
team has been named the World Soccer Team of 1996 by the World
Soccer magazine, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
A report in the latest issue of the leading soccer magazine
said Nigeria topped 47 other teams nominated from various parts of
the world for the award.
</P>
<P>
It said the superlative performance of the team in picking the
gold placed it ahead of the other teams.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's gold medal at the Atlanta Centennial Olympic Games in
August 1996 is the first ever won by an African team. It is also
the first team outside Europe and South America to win the award.
</P>
<P>
The magazine said the margin of Nigeria's success in the world
soccer voting was perhaps a surprise in view of Germany's European
triumph.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria reportedly secured 31.28 points in the poll, whereas
Germany, the current European champions, gained only 19.10 points
to trail it.
</P>
<P>
The coach of the Nigerian team, Bonfrere Jo was voted the ninth
World Best Manager of the year, while the German coach, Berti
Vogts was the World's Number one Manager of the year.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian's team captain and African Footballer of the Year for
1996, Nwankwo Kanu, was voted the eighth Best World Player of the
Year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
