<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Absorbs More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a dynamic economic
center in north China, last year approved 1,109 overseas-funded
projects which attracted a combined contractual investment of 2.5
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
This has brought the total sum of contractual value between
this coastal city in northeast China Liaoning Province and other
countries to 10.66 billion US dollars, said Lin Qingmin, deputy
secretary of the municipal committee of the Chinese Communist
Party.
</P>
<P>
As a part of last year's inflow of investment, more large
projects were built; 89 each involving an investment of 10 million
US dollars. The largest project cost 100 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In addition, most of the new investment was used on hi-tech
projects. And many large state-owned enterprises established joint
ventures with overseas counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Over 600 overseas-funded firms have reinvested their profits
earned in China to expand production scales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
