<HEADLINE> 2 Die, 75 Injured in Road Accident in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Two people died and at least 75
others were injured today when a bus plying from Kirindiwela to
Gampaha hit a bridge and turned turtle, according to Sri Lankan
police sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the mishap had occurred around 6:00 this
morning in Kirindiwela, about 70 kilometers from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the injured were transported to hospital
in police jeeps and with passing vehicles. The people in the
neighborhood also assisted in the rescue operations.  
</P>
