<HEADLINE> S.Africa's Amnesty Committee Gets Torrent of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's Amnesty
Committee of the Truth and Reconciliation Commission (TRC) has
received about 4,500 applications for amnesty, the local daily
"The Star" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Only 11 applications so far have been approved with almost
1500 rejected in terms of the National Promotion of Unity and
Reconciliation Act, the report said.
</P>
<P>
TRC is a special organization authorized by the government
to investigate human right violations occurred during the apartheid
area.
</P>
<P>
However, only some one-fifth of all the amnesty applications
sent to the TRC have involved "killing, abduction, torture or
severe ill treatment", the report quoted TRC spokesman Christelle
Terreblanche as saying.
</P>
<P>
TRC deputy chairman Alex Boraine said earlier the amnesty
committee planned to hear 20-30 cases monthly during the next
five months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
