<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Troops Accelerate Preparations for Stationing in HKSAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Both officers and men in the
Chinese People's Liberation Army, who will be sent to station in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), are diligently
studying numerous laws to prepare themselves for their stationing
there on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Ziren, political commissar of the troops, told reporters
today that his troops understand the importance of learning the
law governing their duties in Hong Kong and the Basic Law as well
as other relevant laws, before they assume their posts in HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, reading material has been made available to every
officer and soldier, covering a range of information such as the
fundamental points of the Basic Law, and questions and answers on
the Garrison Law and Laws on Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past year, Xiong said, the troops have received
training in the laws. Companies at the grassroots level have
enhance the legal awareness of their officers and men through
broadcasts, on bulletin boards, and in a variety of other ways.
</P>
<P>
Now, many officers and men can recite the relevant articles of
the Basic Law and the Garrison Law and fully comprehend these laws.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the troops have also taken various measures to
promote ethical and cultural progress, and to help enable their
officers and soldiers to acquire more knowledge about Hong Kong
regulations and laws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
