<HEADLINE> China Sets New Oil and Gas Production Goals on Land for This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to verify 530
million tons of geological oil reserves, and produce 142 million
tons of crude oil and 17 billion cu. m. of natural gas on land
this year.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national oil meeting, Zhou Yongkang, general
manager of the China Oil and Gas Corporation, said today that the
land oil industrial sector will take measures to stabilize oil
production in the eastern areas and explore the western areas,
while placing equal emphasis on oil and gas production.
</P>
<P>
Oil prospecting will be given top priority this year in a move
to sustain increases in oil reserves and oil output. Existing
oilfields in the eastern areas of China will set out to maintain
their present oil production level, and the western areas will
work even harder to increase oil and gas production.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the production plans of three leading oilfields in
east China, Zhou said that Daqing Oilfield, China's oil giant,
will expand its oil production scale, speed up oil prospecting in
new areas and ensure that the oilfield's output will remain at 56
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Shengli Oilfield in east China's Shandong Province will
actively intensify oil prospecting this year and attempt to slow
down decreases in production to maintain the oil output at 28
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Liaohe Oilfield in northeast China will also work diligently to
keep its oil output at 15 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Jilin Oilfield will enlarge oil production capacity and plans
to produce 3.8 million tons of crude oil, while Huabei, Dagang,
Zhongyuan and Jidong oilfields will take extra steps to find new
oil reserves and make sure that oil production will be stable or
growing.
</P>
<P>
The general manager pinned high hopes on oil prospecting and
development in the western areas of China. Zhou said he believes
that the western areas abound in oil and natural gas resources
that are easy to prospect and these areas will become important
oil production bases for future oil development and production.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang and Changqing oilfields in west China will accelerate
prospecting and increase oil reserves this year, and will produce
8.7 million tons and 3.2 million tons of oil, respectively. Tarim
Oilfield is expected to produce 4.4 million tons of oil, up 1.3
million tons over 1996 level. Turpan-Hami Oilfield is likely to
find new oil reserves and will produce three million tons of oil
this year, according to Zhou.
</P>
<P>
This year's natural gas prospecting and development focus will
be in Sichuan, Shaanxi, Gansu provinces and Ningxia Hui and
Xinjiang Uygur autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
This year will see rapid developments of the first-phase
construction of the gas oilfield in northern Shaanxi Province,
with a production capacity of 1.5 billion cu m, and the building
of another gas oilfield with a production capacity of two billion
cu m in southwest China's Sichuan Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
