<HEADLINE> China Expects 20 Percent Telecom Business Increase in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The telecom market in China
will increase 20 percent this year, keeping China one of the
fastest emerging markets for telecom products in the world,
according to a report released by the Ministry of Electronics
Industry.
</P>
<P>
The report, which appeared in the latest issue of "China
Electronics News", says that domestic demand for
program-controlled switching machines will be 25 million lines
this year, a 25 percent increase over 1996. The market is
gradually being taken over by Chinese suppliers, and the foreign
share is expected to go from 35 percent to 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Mobile phone service is expected to cover all counties in east
China and most prefectures in the west. More than 500,000 channels
will be added to the mobile phone system, 25 percent more than
last year. The number of customers will reach seven million by the
end of 1997, up 35 percent from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Market demand for pagers will be around 2.5 million units, up
85 percent from 1996, and 50,000 private wireless phone systems
will be sold in China this year, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Demand for fax machines is expected to stand at 300,000 this
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
