<HEADLINE> Shanghai Produces More New Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
manufacturing center, is developing more new products to meet the
market needs.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics, the city turned out 25,000
types of new products last year with an added value totalling 50
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai plans to boost the output value of new industrial
products up to 85 billion yuan this year, an increase of 35
billion yuan over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Included will be the output value of motorcycles, elevators,
refrigerators, air-conditioners, microwave ovens, color TVs, food,
common chemical items and clothing.
</P>
<P>
The city will expand its marketing network to the valley of the
Yangtze River, running from west to east, and the western part of
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
