<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Accounting Firm Opens Office in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- An Italian accounting firm has
opened a representative office in Beijing, making Italy the third
European firm to enter into China after France and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Pupilli &AMP; Partners, one of Italy's 70,000 accounting agencies,
is the first Italian accounting firm to establish a permanent
office in China.
</P>
<P>
Luciano Pupilli, senior partner of the Italian firm, said that
the Beijing office is his company's first to open outside Europe.
</P>
<P>
"It is of great significance to promoting Italian-Sino economic
cooperation, especially to boosting Italian investment in China,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The presence of overseas accounting firms in China has helped
improve the country's investment environment, said Ding Pingzhun,
secretary general of the Chinese Institute of Certified Public
Accountants.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen overseas accountance agencies have established a total
of 28 offices in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and a number of
other Chinese cities, according to Ding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
