<HEADLINE> ADF Rebels Reappear in Western Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 17 (xinhua) -- Rebels of Uganda's Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) reappear in Kasese District in
western Uganda not long after they were expelled by the Ugandan
government army in a mop up move, "The Monitor" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Local residents were quoted as saying that they saw some 100
ADF rebels in Kilembe and Muhokya, several kilometers away from
the district town.
</P>
<P>
But security sources confirmed the figure only as 20. The
Ugandan army and local defense units are being mobilized to
remove the ADF represence there, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The ADF established its base in Rwenzori mountain in last
December, but the base has been reportedly uprooted by the Uganda
army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
