<HEADLINE> South Chinese Region Becoming Big Overseas Capital User </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in south China used more than one billion US dollars in
overseas investment in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The region used only 237 million US dollars in 1992 and one
million in 1993.
</P>
<P>
According to Yang Linhai, director of the regional bureau of
foreign trade and economic cooperation, 48 countries and regions
have invested in Guangxi. The top four are Hong Kong, Macao,
Taiwan and the United States.
</P>
<P>
In addition to increasing the number of overseas-funded
tertiary projects, overseas businessmen have put 130 million US
dollars into energy projects and 120 million into infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wenxue, vice-chairman of the region, said that the
opening of the Nanning-Kunming Railway and the return of Hong Kong
to the motherland are two big events that will have an effect on
the region, and that Guangxi will most likely increase overseas
investment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
