<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Meets Mexican Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, member of the
Standing Committee of the Politburo of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), today held a working meeting
with Roque Villanueva, president of Mexico's Institutional
Revolutional Party (PRI).
</P>
<P>
They reviewed relations between the two parties and countries,
and agreed that the increasing contacts between the two sides in
recent years played an active role in promoting friendship between
the two countries and the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Hu, who is also secretary of the CPC Secretariat, said that
Mexico and China share many common points, and with joint efforts
of the two governments in recent years, cooperation between them
have been expanded in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral relationship was ushered into a new era after Mexican
President Ernesto Zedillo's visit to China in 1996, Hu recalled,
stressing that to strengthen party cooperation is crucial to
guarantee a long-term and stable friendship between Mexico and
China.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing with Hu, Roque Villanueva expressed willingness to
expand cooperation with the CPC and the Chinese people, and spoke
highly of the achievements the Chinese people have made under the
leadership of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Also this morning, Hu met a group of Mexican entrepreneurs and
briefed them on China's economic situation and policies.
</P>
<P>
Hu, who arrived here Thursday after a four-day visit to Cuba,
will also go to Colombia on part of his three-nation Latin
American tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
