<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Visits S.Africa on Angola's Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. envoy to Angola,
Alioune Blondin Beye,Thursday met South African Deputy President
Thabo Mbeki on the development of the peace proces in Angola,
local press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki briefed Beye on the recent talks between South African
leaders and Jonas Savimbi, the leader of Angola's former rebel
movement called the National Union for the Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA), said a Foreign Ministry spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Beye, arriving in South Africa Thursday, is also expected to
meet President Nelson Mandela who pledged his support to the
peace process in Angola at a meeting with Savimbi in Umtata in
Eastern Cape Province last week.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki was reportedly planning a trip to Angola next week in an
attempt to continue Mandela's efforts for bringing a lasting
peace solution to the war-torn country.  
</P>
