<HEADLINE> Shanghai Offers Helicopter Tour and Emergence Rescue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Whirly-bird tours of China's
largest city are the latest attraction for tourists.
</P>
<P>
The package, offered by the China General Aviation Corporation,
includes helicopter air tours, patrols, aerial photography, and
traffic control.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of the service is considered highly necessary
not only because of the fast growing tourism, but also because of
the presence of over 2,000 sky-scrapers built or under
construction, which need helicopters in case of fire and other
emergencies.
</P>
<P>
US-made Bell helicopters will be used for the new service.
</P>
