<HEADLINE> Tanzanian NBC To Split Into Three Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 17 ( Xinhua) --The Tanzanian government
has decided to split the National Bank of Commerce (NBC) into
three subsidiary banks under one holding company, Acting Finance
Minister Daniel Yona said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Yona told the NBC Board of Directors and Management
That the proposed strategy will remove the government as the sole
shareholder of the NBC.
</P>
<P>
"The reorganization proposal is to create within the NBC three
subsidiaries, each composed of a network of NBC branches," he
said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Tanzanian government is about to
adopt a privatisation proposal for the NBC, with its top
management continuing to discount the suggestions.
</P>
<P>
Yona said that the NBC with its network of about 130 branches
will remian the holdigng company.
</P>
<P>
The reorganization plan will place the institution into
private sector, 30 years after a series of private banks were
nationalised to create the sprawling state commercial bank.
</P>
<P>
Yona said that re-organization and re-capitalization of the
NBC have been designed to maximize the benefits of NBC's
restructuring on savings and effciency.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government is seeking investors to inject
capital in the new banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
