<HEADLINE> 20 Killed in Road Accident in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 17 (Xinhua) -- A road crash killed 20
people, including a pregnant woman and her five-year-old girl, at
Bwawani in Coast Region on Thursday morning,
local press said today.
</P>
<P>
The number of the wounded reached at least 16. Three of them
are still in critical condition in nearby Morogoro regional
Hospital, said Elizabeth Edward, the acting Morogoro Regional
Police Commander.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa expressed "profound shock"
at the tragedy later Thursday in a message of condolence to the
bereaved families and promised to take concrete measures against
overspeeding and reckless driving.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims were on a Dar es Salaam-bound bus which
left Morogoro, about 300 kilometers west of the capital, at 6:30
a.m., and collided with an oncoming lorry with a trailer about
half an hour later, killing 16 on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The bus driver, who survived and was being sought by the
police, had allegedly attempted to overtake a Suzuki Station
Wagon near a corner when the lorry with a trailer emerged
suddenly on the opposition direction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
