<HEADLINE> 14 Killed in Bus Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen people were killed and
33 others injured when a Dhaka-bound passenger night coach
Thursday plunged into a road-side ditch on Dhaka-Nagarbari highway
in the Barak area, about 90 kilometers northwest of Dhaka,
according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Of the dead, 13 passengers of the bus died on the spot while
one person succumbed to his injuries in the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina in a condolence message on
Thursday night expressed her deep shock at the road accident and
wished early recovery of the injured persons.
</P>
<P>
All the injured persons were admitted to hospital while the
driver of the bus managed to escape.
</P>
<P>
An injured passenger claimed that the accident occurred as the
driver of the night coach was drunk and lost control over the
steering.  
</P>
</TEXT>
