<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Condemns Clinic Bombing in Atlanta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton today condemned the explosions at an abortion clinic in
Atlanta as a "vile and malevolent crime" and vowed the
perpetrators would be severly punished.
</P>
<P>
"Anyone who brings violence against a woman trying to exercise
her constitutional rights is committing an act of terror. It is
always wrong. And it should be punished severely," Clinton said in
a written statement.
</P>
<P>
"Nobody has a right to use violence in America to advance their
own convictions over the rights of others." he said, adding "We
will get to the bottom of this, and we will punish those
responsible to the fullest extent the law provides."
</P>
<P>
Two explosions erupted inside and outside a building housing
the Atlanta Northside Family Planning Services, injuring six
people including an agent of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and
Firearms.
</P>
<P>
An investigation was under way, and police said that it appeared
that the abortion clinic was the target of the explosion. Half
an hour after the second explosion, the Piedmont Clinic, another
abortion center in the city was evacuated after receiving a bomb
threat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
