<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Boost Development in Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in
Mongolia has reached 123 million U.S. dollars and the number of
foreign joint ventures or wholly foreign-funded enterprises has
grown to 544, the Montsame News Agency reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Mongolian-Chinese joint ventures account for 30 percent, or
170, of the foreign-invested enterprises, followed by Russian and
Japanese funded businesses.
</P>
<P>
The target of foreign investment has switched from the early
1990s favorites of food and services. Now, most foreign investment
is going into research, information consultancy, building
materials, wool manufacturing, electricity and telecommunications,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia is trying to improve its infrastructure with loans
provided by Japan, the World Bank and Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian State Great Hural (parliament) recently decided
to set up a committee to handle foreign investment. 
</P>
