<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HIV Virus Carriers Now Over 2,000 in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 16 (Xinhua) -- HIV virus carriers now number
2,105 people in Russia, of which, nearly half were infected last
year with the virus that leads to AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Public Health Ministry announced this at a
press conference today. They attributed it mainly to more and
more drug addicts being infected by the Acquired Immune Deficiency
Syndrome (AIDS).
</P>
<P>
Drug-takers usually shared syringes when they got intravenous
injections, making it very possible to spread the virus, they said.
</P>
<P>
Drug addicts infected with the virus increased from three in
the first six months of last year to 600 in the last six months of
the year, the experts said.
</P>
<P>
They predicted that about 100,000 people in Russia would be
infected with the virus by the end of this year, and the figure
would soar to 500,000 next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
