<HEADLINE> Nationwide Support for Development in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese central government
and local governments in other parts of China have helped Tibet
Autonomous Region complete 56 projects over the past two years, in
a drive to aid its development.
</P>
<P>
Six other projects are still under construction in Tibet. This
scale of construction has never been seen before in the region,
said local officials.
</P>
<P>
To help with the projects, 165 teams of workers have been sent
to the region. The projects cost a total investment of 3.52
billion yuan (about 424 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The 56 projects mean that Tibetans will have an additional 206
million kilowatt hours of electricity annually, and seven counties
will be lit up at night.
</P>
<P>
Radio programs reach 55 percent of the people in Tibet and TV
is now seen by 45 percent of the Tibetans.
</P>
<P>
A fiber cable has been laid Between Lhasa and Xigaze, and in
Zedang and Xigaze, children have less difficulties in attending
primary school now. 
</P>
