<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 16 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government will
start implementing the rules of equal rights between men and women
enunciated in the Fourth World Conference on Women held in China
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Rosiska Darcy, president of the National Council for Women's
Rights of Brazil (CNDMB), expressed hope that the equality policy
will radically improve the situation of Brazilian women.
</P>
<P>
A document drafted by the CNDMB which will be the basis for
the implementation of the rules was discussed today in the Justice
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Darcy said equal rights between men and women would perfect the
democratic state and guarantee human rights.
</P>
<P>
"Not only Brazil, but all the countries of the world need to
promote the integrated works to re-establish the equality of men
and women."
</P>
<P>
She stressed that the world needed to work out effective
policies to fight against violence and discrimination against
women, and strive for the creation of institutional mechanisms to
support those policies. 
