<HEADLINE> Largest-Scale Sculptures Being Built in Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 ( Xinhua) -- China's coastal city of
Qingdao in Shandong Province is providing the largest number of
sculptures in the country, Guangming Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen new sculpture-concentrated areas will be set up near
the city's tourist attractions, with the biggest one covering
about ten ha in front of the city government building.
</P>
<P>
The sculptures will mainly depict noteworthy figures or
incidents from Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
Early this month, people from 20 art schools hurried to Qingdao
to offer bids to participate in the city's large-scale sculpture
project.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the sculptures, which will cost 80
million yuan (9.6 million US dollars), are expected to be
completed by the end of the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
