<HEADLINE> China To Import 58 Million Dollars Worth of Motorola Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 17 (Xinhua) -- China is going to get the
latest of digital mobile telephone systems from Motorola, one of
the leading telecom suppliers in the United States.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest issue of People's Posts and
Telecommunications News, the 58-million-dollar contract for GSM
(global service for mobile communication) equipment was concluded
in Beijing with two Chinese buyers - Orient Telecom, the country's
biggest listed telecom company, and Zhejiang Technology Import and
Export Co., Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The contract stipulates that the US company will supply Orient
with M-Cell 2 and M-Cell 6 base stations, and technical support
ranging from professional training to industrial design and
manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Orient is also authorized to manufacture and sell Motorola's
cellular telecom products, like GSM, TACS, and CDMA (code
diversion multiple access) equipment, in China, and to provide
technical support nationwide, the paper said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
