<HEADLINE> Michael Johnson Wins Jesse Owens Trophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Michael Johnson, Olympic
double champion in the 200 and 400 meters, became the first
athlete to win the Jesse Owens International Trophy twice.
</P>
<P>
After his sweep in the sprint events in Atlanta, Johnson
received the most votes for the 1996 trophy for the second
consecutive year.
</P>
<P>
Swimmer Michelle Smith of Ireland was second in the voting, and
weightlifter Naim Suleymanoglu of Turkey was third.
</P>
<P>
Johnson set the world record of 19.32 seconds in the 200 meters
and an Olympic record of 43.49 in the 400 meters.
</P>
<P>
Chinese woman runner Wang Junxia was the first Asian athlete to
win the trophy in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
