<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Winter Cold Kills 205 in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Extreme winter cold has
killed 205 people in Mexico and damaged at least 58,000 hectares
of crops across the country.
</P>
<P>
The worst affected northern states are Chihuahua (87 dead),
Nuevo Leon, Tamaulipas, Coahuila, Sinaloa, and Sonora.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities said 17 people died of cold in the state of
Durango, 34 in the state of Mexico, 23 in Nuevo Leon, 16 in
Coahuila, 14 in Tamaulipas, 12 in Sonora, one in Michoacan, and
another in Aguascalientes.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims died of respiratory problems caused by the
unusual cold or were frozen to death.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers said the damaged agricultural products were
mainly watermelon, bean pods and chile, mango, banana, lemon,
and cucumber.
</P>
<P>
Frost damaged 2,000 hectares of strawberry crops in the Bajio
zone.
</P>
<P>
The Communications and Transports Ministry ordered 23 ports in
the Gulf of Mexico closed to maritime activities, on Monday,
because the cold front caused winds of up to 75 kph. and
three-meter high waves.
</P>
<P>
The National Meteorological Service forecast today that another
cold current is advancing toward the country's northern borders
and can possibly deal another severe cold blow to the Gulf and
central Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
