<HEADLINE> Weah May Boycott FIFA Award Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Liberian soccer player George Weah
said he may boycott the awarding ceremony of FIFA'S Fair Play in
Lisbon this year due to a legal action against him.
</P>
<P>
"At the moment I am not really planning to go to Lisbon on
Monday," said Weah, the 1995 FIFA world player of the year.
</P>
<P>
During a European Champions' League match in Portugal, Weah of
AC Milan was accused of butting Portuguese Jorge Costa in head and
the latter has filed a suit against the "Fair Play" winner.
</P>
<P>
"Jorge Costa has still not withdrawn his legal action and, by
going to Portugal, I would face not only legal risks but also an
enormous amount of local pressure," Weah said.
</P>
<P>
And Weah has expressed his worries to FIFA general secretary
Sepp Blatter, requesting guarantees from Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Last month Weah apologised to FIFA for his rude behavior which
led to his six-match ban. 
</P>
