<HEADLINE> Mexico City To Host Disabled Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Mexico City will host the
Second International Congress for Disabled Persons from March 12
to 14, the Federal District Assembly's Commission for Attention to
Vulnerable Groups said today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, organized by the Mexican Autism Society and the
National System for the Integral Development of the Family (DIF),
is called to promote measures that will provide disabled people
with access to the labor market.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to call for the ratification of Accord
159 of the International Labor Organization (ILO), which sets down
the right of the disabled to be admitted into the labor market.
</P>
<P>
Ignacio Leon Robles, president of the association, said tax
rebates will be promoted to encourage companies to implement
programs for training disabled people to provide them with working
skills.
</P>
<P>
One of the obstacles these persons met when they tried to enter
the labor market was the lack of training and of sensibility on
the part of employers, Robles said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
