<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The following are top stories in
leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Business World
</P>
<P>
-- A regional center for biodiversity conservation, to be
supported by the European Union, will be set up in the Philippines
within the year.
</P>
<P>
Malaya
</P>
<P>
-- Consumers will have to pay higher minimum monthly fees for
local calls as telephone companies in the Philippines hike basic
charges by 20 percent starting this year.
</P>
<P>
Today
</P>
<P>
-- After chalking up double-digit increase in September 1996,
growth in the Philippines' domestic manufacturing slid again to
single-digit levels in October last year, indicating a possible
slowdown in the manufacturing sector which government has
identified as a key engine of economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Times
</P>
<P>
-- Proceeds from the Philippine government's privatization
program fell 74 percent below the target last year due to delays
in the sale of big-ticket items such as the Food Terminal Inc. and
shares in Manila Electric Co.  
</P>
