<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Salt Lake Expects 800m in Olympic Sponsors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Organizers for the 2002
Winter Olympics in Salt Lake City hoped to allure a record of 800
million US dollars in sponsorship, officials said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The money will be raised under a joint marketing agreement
between the US Olympic Committee (USOC) and the Organizing
Committee, according to USOC deputy general secretary John Krimsky.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was mapped out after a year of negotiations and
will be approved by the International Olympic Committee, Krimsky
said.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Salt Lake City will have a 70-percent
share of cash in corporate sponsorships until a figure of 244
million US dollars is reached.
</P>
<P>
Then, it will receive a 30-percent share until organizers
collect another 10 million US dollars. After that, the USOC will
keep most of the cash.
</P>
<P>
Sponsorships for the Atlanta Games were about 800 million US
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
