<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Rebound to New Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street edged to
new highs today after recovering from an afternoon pullback
spurred by another increase in interest rates in a jittery bond
market.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average gained 38.49 to 6,765.37,
barely beating Tuesday's record finish at 6,762.29.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip barometer set its seventh new high in nine
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by nearly an 8-to-7
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, with its volume reaching
532.31 million shares, slightly more than 525.02 million in the
previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 2.55 to 769.75, and
the NYSE's composite index rose 1.08 to 406.12, both setting new
highs.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 6.93 to 1,340.46, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 0.88 to 587.36.
</P>
<P>
Computer-related issues led the early advance as investors
reacted enthusiastically to more better-than-expected earnings
news from leading technology concerns such as Sun Microsystems and
Digital Equipment.
</P>
<P>
Bonds moved lower in the morning after the Labor Department
reported that the number of first-time claims for jobless benefits
fell last week to a three-month low.
</P>
<P>
As bonds fell today, the yield on the 30-year Treasury bond
rose from late Wednesday's 6.79 percent to nearly 6.86 percent
before settling at about 6.83 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
