<DOCNO> XIE19970117.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Export Insurance Group Says Asia Remains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- Despite the slow-down of its
economic growth, Asia remains the most attractive market for
French enterprises to sell their consumption products and
equipments, the French export insurance group, Compagnie Francaise
pour le Commerce Exterieur (COFACE), said today.
</P>
<P>
"China, South Korea, Thailand, (the Chinese province of)
Taiwan, Indonesia, India, Malaysia, Hong Kong and Singapore figure
among the all primary priorities'' for French enterprises to
export their products, said the study by COFACE.
</P>
<P>
Describing the Asian market as having "the strongest potential
of development" in the world, the COFACE said that except in
Vietnam, Pakistan and Myanmar, French enterprises can have
business there with weak or moderate risks.
</P>
<P>
Citing statistics from the World Bank, COFACE said that by the
year 2005, Asia -- without taking into account Japan -- will be
the biggest producer in the world in terms of the real purchasing
power of its local population.
</P>
<P>
The overall production of the region will by then attain 31
percent of the world's total, surpassing the United States, Europe
and Japan respectively.
</P>
<P>
It said that China's growth remains strong, while its exports,
imports and foreign investments are impressive, and its reserve of
hard currencies have attained record high.
</P>
<P>
The COFACE has a 50 billion franc (10 billion U.S. dollars)
business in China and signed with China several big insurance
contracts, including those over the Daya Bay nuclear power station
and China's purchase of 30 Airbus passenger carriers last year.
</P>
<P>
French enterprises only have a 2 percent share of the Asian
market, but the latter has 40 percent of the big insurance
contracts opportunities in the world, said COFACE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
