<HEADLINE> France Presents Candidates for Head of UN Peace-Keeping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 16 (Xinhua) -- France has presented to the new
United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan two candidates to take
over the U.N. Peace-Keeping Operations Department.
</P>
<P>
Bernard Miyet, 50, and Marc Perrin de Brichambaut, 48, met with
Annan last week in the U.N. headquarters in New York, the Agence
France-Presse (AFP) quoted diplomatic sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Miyet now serves as France's permanent representative at the
Vienna-based Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe,
and de Brichambaut is the head of the Department of Legal Affairs
of the French Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Annan, who has been serving as the head of the U.N.
Peace-Keeping Operations Department, announced one day after his
election in December that a Frenchman would serve as an assistant
U.N. secretary general in charge of peace-keeping operations.
</P>
<P>
The Peace-Keeping Operations Department, and the Political
Affairs Department -- which is headed by a British -- are two most
important departments of the U.N.. 
</P>
